}
</code></pre><p sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/controller-methods-views.md" sourcestartlinenumber="60" sourceendlinenumber="60">Notice how the view template has a <code>@model MvcMovie.Models.Movie</code> statement at the top of the file. <code>@model MvcMovie.Models.Movie</code> specifies that the view expects the model for the view template to be of type <code>Movie</code>.</p>
<p sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/controller-methods-views.md" sourcestartlinenumber="62" sourceendlinenumber="62">The scaffolded code uses several Tag Helper methods to streamline the HTML markup. The - <a class="xref" href="../../mvc/views/working-with-forms.html" data-raw-source="[Label Tag Helper](xref:mvc/views/working-with-forms)" sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/controller-methods-views.md" sourcestartlinenumber="62" sourceendlinenumber="62">Label Tag Helper</a> displays the name of the field (&quot;Title&quot;, &quot;ReleaseDate&quot;, &quot;Genre&quot;, or &quot;Price&quot;). The <a class="xref" href="../../mvc/views/working-with-forms.html" data-raw-source="[Input Tag Helper](xref:mvc/views/working-with-forms)" sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/controller-methods-views.md" sourcestartlinenumber="62" sourceendlinenumber="62">Input Tag Helper</a> renders an HTML <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> element. The <a class="xref" href="../../mvc/views/working-with-forms.html" data-raw-source="[Validation Tag Helper](xref:mvc/views/working-with-forms)" sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/controller-methods-views.md" sourcestartlinenumber="62" sourceendlinenumber="62">Validation Tag Helper</a> displays any validation messages associated with that property.</p>
